<HEADLINE>
<P>
INFLATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Controlling inflation is in our best long-term interest. Inflation is an 
insidious, pernicious disease that erodes the financial foundation of a nation. 
</P>
<P>
 The ills of inflation aren't readily apparent but that doesn't mean they are 
not destructive (letters, Sept. 7). Actual example: A retired couple sell their 
home in 1976 for $20,000 to move to a mobile home park. Three years later the 
buyer of their home resells it for $60,000 and the retired couple are having a 
tough time paying escalating ground rent for their mobile home. Meanwhile, 
investors dissatisfied with real estate returns are turning to the precious 
metal markets for quicker profits. And the silliness hit the low point when 
supposedly prudent people started investing in pyramids! Have we forgotten? 
We're lucky to have the Volckers and Greenspans who haven't. 
</P>
<P>
 ARTHUR DAWSON 
</P>
<P>
 Hermosa Beach 
</P>
