<HEADLINE>
<P>
DISTRAUGHT DEPUTY KILLS WIFE, THEN HIMSELF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A sheriff's deputy, distraught over the impending breakup of his marriage, 
shot and killed his wife Thursday in the courthouse then killed himself in a 
standoff with police, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police Lt. Tommy Cicardo said Paul Broussard, 39, killed his 26-year-old wife, 
Andrea, in a stairwell of the Rapides Parish Courthouse where she worked in the 
clerk's office. 
</P>
<P>
 "He ran from the scene on foot and we caught up with him about a block away in 
front of a local bank," Cicardo said. "After several hours of negotiation, with 
him holding a gun to his head or to his chest, he shot himself in the head 
shortly before noon." 
</P>
<P>
 The couple had a 2-year-old child and he had a 10-year-old child by a previous 
marriage, Cicardo said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
