<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE NATION; ARMY CAN'T STOP BALDWIN, 
DUKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rob Baldwin scored three touchdowns to help Duke defeat Army, 43-7, at Durham, 
N.C. 
</P>
<P>
 Baldwin's scoring runs of seven, three and two yards give him seven touchdowns 
after three games, the best performance by a Blue Devil running back since 
Randy Cuthbert rushed for 10 touchdowns in the entire 1989 season. Duke is 3-0; 
Army 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The NCAA restored the eligibility of two of the five suspended Florida State 
football players, freeing All-American linebacker Derrick Brooks and reserve 
offensive lineman Marcus Long to play Saturday at Wake Forest. However, the 
NCAA extended the two-game suspension of senior tailback Tiger McMillon to 
three games. Florida State appealed the decision on McMillon and said a ruling 
was expected today. Patrick McNeil, a three-year starter at guard, had been 
suspended for three games but he will also sit out a fourth for an unspecified 
violation of team rules. Forrest Conoly had been suspended for four games. All 
were disciplined for taking gifts from a prospective agent last November. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Miami defensive end Rusty Medearis, who fought his way back from a major knee 
injury two years ago to start in the Hurricanes' first two games this season, 
has ended his comeback attempt because of chronic pain. 
</P>
