</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Soccer 
</P>
<P>
 Ralph Black of the Splash was named to the All-CISL team, selected by league 
coaches. 
</P>
<P>
 Black, a defender who scored 35 points in 26 games and registered 36 blocks, 
joined a Dallas trio, goalkeeper Joe Papaleo and forwards David Doyle and Tatu 
as well as Washington midfielder Goran Hunjak and Arizona defender Terry 
Woodberry on the first team. 
</P>
<P>
 The league also changed the date of the Splash's second playoff game against 
Las Vegas in the CISL semifinals. Game 1 starts at 7:35 tonight at The Pond of 
Anaheim. Game 2 starts at 6:05 p.m. Sunday at the Thomas & Mack Center; it had 
previously been scheduled for Saturday. The third game, if necessary, will be 
Wednesday at The Pond. 
</P>
<P>
 The winner will play the Dallas-Washington winner. MARTIN HENDERSON 
