<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; RAMS; HENLEY MAKES RETURN TO THE STARTING LINEUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Darryl Henley was in the starting lineup Thursday in place of cornerback Steve 
Israel, who has been bothered by tendinitis in his knee, the result of chasing 
Atlanta's Andre Rison all over the field last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Coach Chuck Knox said he wasn't sure who would start the game against the 
49ers. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have to wait and see how Israel's tendinitis is," Knox said. "We'll see 
who is ready and able on Sunday morning." 
</P>
<P>
 Defensive tackle Jimmie Jones missed practice because of a sore toe. Jones 
hurt his toe in Atlanta and it was stepped on in Wednesday's practice. 
</P>
