 Bruce Johnson's 18-yard touchdown pass to Hoa Le with 39 seconds remaining 
Thursday lifted the Lobos to a 12-10 nonleague victory over Oxnard at Palmdale 
High. 
</P>
<P>
 Last week, Littlerock (1-0-1) escaped with a 14-14 tie against Serrano when 
the Lobo defense recovered a fumble at its goal line with 33 seconds remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 Thursday, the Lobos again capitalized on a turnover late in the game to beat 
Oxnard (0-2). Mike Stewart recovered a fumble at the Lobos' 36 with three 
minutes remaining. Johnson then directed a 64-yard scoring drive that was kept 
alive by three converted fourth downs. 
</P>
<P>
 After a scoreless first half, Littlerock's Lafayette Bailey returned the 
