<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-NURSE DENIES 3 MOLESTATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A former nurse at St. John's Regional Medical Center pleaded not guilty 
Thursday to three counts of sexual battery on patients while they were sedated. 
</P>
<P>
 Gorden Butikofer, 37, appeared calm and chatted with his attorney as he waited 
for Thursday's arraignment before Ventura County Municipal Judge Herbert Curtis 
III. 
</P>
<P>
 While a registered nurse at the Oxnard hospital between January, 1993, and 
this May, Butikofer fondled three Ventura County men who were receiving 
treatment, authorities said. Each alleged victim was in his 20s. 
</P>
<P>
 Curtis lowered Butikofer's bail from $25,000 to $10,000. Prosecutors did not 
object to the bail reduction. 
</P>
<P>
 In court, Deputy Dist. Atty. Bob Calvert said all three victims will testify 
against Butikofer during a preliminary hearing Oct. 12. 
</P>
<P>
 Court officials said that Butikofer lives in Utah. He has no criminal history, 
they said. Butikofer was arrested by Oxnard police at Los Angeles International 
Airport on Tuesday night, when he arrived to catch a plane to Mexico with some 
St. John's hospital employees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
