<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The county's amusement parks, beaches and other attractions really draw 
people. 
</P>
<P>
 In 1993, 37.8 million people visited Orange County during vacations or for 
business. 
</P>
<P>
 Travel generated $4.8 billion in 1993 and brought in $71 million in local tax 
revenue, according to the Anaheim/Orange County Visitor & Convention Bureau. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousands of people are supported by the travel business, from hotel workers 
to printers. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the top draws are Disneyland, Knott's Berry Farm and the coastal areas 
around Newport Beach and the South County area. Today 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Beach's SeaFest celebration continues today with a food tasting event 
and an antique show. 
</P>
<P>
 The Taste of Newport, which costs $6 per person, runs from 5 to 11 p.m. It 
includes food samples from 34 local restaurants as well as live music. The 
Antique Seafair exhibit and sale runs from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 An exhibit also will be presented at Newport Beach's Nautical Museum from 10 
a.m. to 3 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The SeaFest is being held at locations throughout Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 729-4400. 
</P>
