 One afternoon, reader Matt Chicklo of Trabuco Canyon needed to tidy up his 
garage, so he left his 5-year-old son, Marc, to look after his 3-year-old twin 
brothers in the living room. Matt told Marc to come get him if things "got out 
of control": 
</P>
<P>
 Within 15 minutes, the garage door flew open and Marc, TV clicker in hand, 
wailed: "Dad, come quick, the twins are out of remote control."  
