<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; DEPUTY 
SHOOTS, KILLS MAN WHO ALLEGEDLY PULLED KNIFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 43-year-old man was shot to death by a sheriff's deputy Thursday after the 
man allegedly pulled a knife on the deputy's partner at an apartment house near 
MacArthur Park, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy Britta Tubbs, a spokeswoman for the Sheriff's Department, said the 
incident occurred at 11:50 a.m. while the deputies were conducting a check on a 
work-release inmate living at the complex at 1036 S. Menlo Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Tubbs said the deputies, one male, the other female, had just finished their 
assignment and were leaving the building in single file when a man shoved the 
male deputy past a self-locking security gate and then pulled the door shut, 
trapping himself with the female deputy. 
</P>
<P>
 He lunged at her and she was able to fend him off, but the man pulled a 6-inch 
steak knife and tried to stab her, Tubbs said. As they struggled, Tubbs said, 
the male deputy fired several rounds through the security door, wounding the 
man in the upper torso. 
</P>
<P>
 The assailant -- who was not identified pending family notification -- was 
taken to California Hospital, where he was pronounced dead. Tubbs said the dead 
man was not the inmate the deputies had checked on. The deputies were not 
identified. 
</P>
</TEXT>
