<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; RAMS; HENLEY GETS EXTENSION TO RAISE ADDED BAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK PLATTE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The deadline for cornerback Darryl Henley to come up with an additional 
$40,000 in bail associated with his criminal case has been extended to 
Wednesday, a federal judge has ruled. 
</P>
<P>
 Henley, indicted last year on cocaine conspiracy charges, had until today to 
come up with the additional amount to keep himself out of jail. But U.S. 
District Court Judge Gary L. Taylor granted Henley's request for a deadline 
extension. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams already have agreed to post a $2-million bond on Henley's behalf 
during the time he is traveling with the team. But Taylor raised a separate 
bond amount that applies to the time that Henley is in Southern California. 
MARK PLATTE 
</P>
</TEXT>
