<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEAD MAN FOUND AT UCI IS IDENTIFIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man found dead on the UC Irvine campus was identified Thursday as Robert 
Carlos Avila, a 34-year-old transient. 
</P>
<P>
 Coroner's investigators said it will take further chemical tests to determine 
how Avila died. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said there was no evidence of foul play. 
</P>
<P>
 Avila's body was spotted by a motorist Wednesday on a slope near a playing 
field at University Drive and Mesa Road. 
</P>
<P>
 A makeshift encampment that may have been his home was discovered behind 
nearby bushes. 
</P>
