</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Raytheon Announces Consolidation, Job Cuts: The Lexington, Mass.-based company 
said it would cut 940 jobs in the United States and Britain as it combines its 
Beech Aircraft and Corporate Jet subsidiaries into one aviation business to be 
called Raytheon Aircraft Co.Weak demand in the business aviation market 
prompted the company to seek ways to lower costs. The firm said it would cut 
450 jobs in Wichita, Kan.; 140 in Little Rock, Ark., 40 in Salina, Kan., and 
310 in England. Raytheon Corp. acquired Beech in 1980 and bought Raytheon 
Corporate Jets from British Aerospace about a year ago. The company also said 
it would move the final assembly and engineering and support activities for the 
Hawker mid-size jets -- made by Raytheon Corporate Jets -- from Britain to 
Wichita. 
