BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 QVC Takeover Hits Snag: The cash tender offer by cable TV operators Comcast 
Corp. and Tele-Communications Inc. for the home shopping network firm will 
likely be delayed until at least late October or early November, a source said, 
due to further antitrust scrutiny by the Federal Trade Commission of TCI's 
controlling stake in rival Home Shopping Network. As reported first by the 
Washington Post, federal regulators are considering a challenge to the proposed 
purchase of QVC because of TCI's role.If TCI bows out, more bidders might 
surface. Sources said that in the earlier round, would-be rivals did not want 
to anger TCI because it controls more than a fifth of the nation's subscribers 
and might drop QVC from its systems. 
</P>
