<TEXT>
<P>
 IBM May Delay Introduction of PowerPC Computer: International Business 
Machines Corp. may delay introduction of the computers until early 1995 to 
coincide with the release of a new version of OS/2, the operating system 
software necessary to control the basic functions of the computers, a source 
close to the company said. A version of OS/2 geared toward IBM's PowerPC-based 
PCs isn't scheduled to be released until the middle of next year.Armonk, 
N.Y.-based IBM previously had said it would introduce the computers by the end 
of the year. A spokeswoman wouldn't say when the machines would be released. 
PowerPC News, a newsletter distributed through the Internet, reported that the 
three PowerPC-based machines would be delayed until February. 
</P>
