<TEXT>
<P>
 Ford Raises Prices Slightly on '95 Models: The auto maker said prices of its 
new model year cars and trucks will average 0.1% more than the pre-introduction 
prices announced earlier this summer.With the hike, which amounts to about $22 
per vehicle, Ford's average vehicle prices for 1995 are up an average of 1.4%, 
or $281, from final 1994 prices. Ford's move is the latest in a series of price 
boosts by U.S. and Japanese auto makers. In July, General Motors hiked prices 
of its 1995 models an average 2.5%, or $494 per vehicle, and Chrysler announced 
price increases averaging 2%. 
</P>
