<P>
 One-Year T-Bill Rate Rises: The average discount rate was 5.38%, up from 5.36% 
at the last auction on Aug. 18.It was the highest rate since 52-week bills 
averaged 5.88% on July 25, 1991. The bills will carry an equivalent coupon 
interest rate of 5.69% with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,456. 
Sales totaled $16.76 billion out of bids of $53.41 billion. 
