<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Abbey Healthcare Group Inc.: The Costa Mesa company recently completed 
acquisition of eight respiratory therapy companies, bringing to 20 the number 
of such companies it has purchased this year. 
</P>
<P>
 Terms of the latest acquisitions were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 Abbey now owns Med-America Healthcare Associates Inc. in North Platte, Neb.; 
Stat Home Care in Dallas; North Shores Medical in Ft. Bragg, ; Safecare Medical 
in St. Louis; South Texas Stat Care in Houston; Smoky Mountain Medical in 
Jefferson City, Tenn.; Franklin Home Oxygen in Nashville, Tenn.; and Sandia 
Home Medical in Albuquerque, N.M. The new operations will be integrated with 
existing Abbey offices. 
</P>
<P>
 Abbey Healthcare Group provides in-home health care, such as respiratory 
therapy and infusion therapy, for patients who have been discharged from 
hospitals but need ongoing treatment. 
</P>
