<TEXT>
<P>
 Union to Renegotiate Package: The severance package remains an open issue, 
however, for the thousand or so union workers at Hughes in Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 The reason: In 1992, Hughes workers represented by the Carpenters Union voted 
down the severance package offered then, opting instead to take a higher 
company-paid matching contribution to their 401(k) savings plans. "That was a 
big mistake," said one former union steward. 
</P>
<P>
 Given that vote in 1992, the Carpenters Union must now negotiate a severance 
package for its members. The union's contract with Hughes expires in early 
November. 
