<TEXT>
<P>
 Sam's Club to Vote: The National Labor Relations Board has set Oct. 7 as the 
date when about 150 workers at Sam's Club in Fullerton will vote on whether 
they want to be represented by Teamsters Local 952. 
</P>
<P>
 If a majority of these warehouse and clerical workers cast ballots for the 
Teamsters, it will mark the first store owned by discount giant Wal-Mart to 
become unionized.The Arkansas-based retailer operates 430 Sam's Club warehouses 
and some 2,300 Wal-Mart stores in the country, but not a single one is under a 
union contract. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange-based Teamsters Local 952 filed for a union election in late July after 
months of organizing. At that time, the union said it had signatures of support 
from the majority of the workers at the Fullerton store. But the election will 
tell whether that support has held steady or waned. 
