<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: DIP IN MICROSEMI INVENTORY VALUE LEADS TO CHARGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Microsemi Corp. said it will record an $8-million to $10-million charge in its 
fourth quarter to reduce the carrying value of military-related inventories and 
other assets where there has been a permanent reduction of value. 
</P>
<P>
 Microsemi said substantially all the charges result directly from changes in 
military procurement policies and practices that call for the use of commercial 
products rather than a mandatory use of military standard parts. 
</P>
<P>
 The company reported net income of $950,000, or 12 cents a share, on sales of 
$29,830,000 in the year-ago fourth quarter ended Oct. 3, 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 Microsemi said uncertainties caused by the Department of Defense's changes in 
defense procurement policy make it necessary to revalue certain inventories to 
current market value. 
</P>
</TEXT>
